  (text_box "Description: Vehicle Input Protection. Front end for the 12 V automotive line: fuse F1 (2 A), reverse-polarity P-FET Q1 (gate pull-down R15, gate-source Zener clamp D6 15 V), transient suppressor D7 (TVS), and bulk cap C12, producing the protected TPS54360_VIN."
    (at 142.24 83.82 0) (size 81.28 10.16)
    (stroke (width 0) (type default))
    (fill (type color) (color 255 255 194 1))
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27) bold) (justify left top))
    (uuid 02f142f5-0769-4f8d-9bfe-96d5a7690e03)
  )
  (text_box "Description: +5.5 V Buck-Boost (pre-regulator). Buck-boost regulator (U6, TPS63802) generating a 5.5 V intermediate rail from BQ24075_OUT. Because OUT swings 3.0-4.8 V - straddling the target - a buck-boost is used so it regulates cleanly whether the input is below or near the output. The 5.5 V output feeds the ADP7142 LDO, which cleans it down to the final +5 V analog rail (op-amp positive supply and the −5 V charge-pump stage); the extra 0.5 V gives the LDO its dropout headroom. Inductor L4 bridges the L1/L2 switch nodes; R21/R22 set the 5.5 V output via the FB divider (R21 = 910 k, R22 = 91 k); R23 enables the device; C18/C19 provide input/output decoupling."
    (at 25.4 220.98 0) (size 111.76 15.24)
    (stroke (width 0) (type default))
    (fill (type color) (color 255 255 194 1))
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27) bold) (justify left top))
    (uuid 06675564-38c8-4b2f-ba01-3e77a0f9089a)
  )
  (text_box "Description:\n\nUSB-C receptacle (J1) providing the 5 V bench/charging port.\nCC1/CC2 pulled down by R1/R2 (5.1 kΩ) to advertise a sink/UFP role;\nD+/D− pass through the ESD/TVS array (U1) to USBC_D±;\nVBUS is brought out as USBC_VOUT to the source-OR."
    (at 25.4 30.48 0) (size 35.56 25.4)
    (stroke (width 0) (type default))
    (fill (type color) (color 255 255 194 1))
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27) (thickness 0.254) bold) (justify left top))
    (uuid 1aceac7f-c7a8-4818-9a83-14c5a4b0d4cf)
  )
  (text_box "Description: −5 V Analog Rail (inverting LDO charge pump). Regulated negative-supply generator (U7, LM27761) producing a clean −5 V (LM27761_VOUT) from the +5 V rail, for the negative op-amp supply in the analog front end. The device inverts +5 V with an internal switched-capacitor charge pump (flying cap C15 on C+/C−) and regulates/cleans the result with its built-in LDO. C16 is the input cap, C17 the output cap, and R19/R20 set the regulated output magnitude via the VFB divider. EN is tied to VIN (always on)."
    (at 142.24 162.56 0) (size 83.82 15.24)
    (stroke (width 0) (type default))
    (fill (type color) (color 255 255 194 1))
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27) bold) (justify left top))
    (uuid 23c03107-bdcd-4719-8a45-bb7b9065620c)
  )
  (text_box "Description: Clean +5 V Analog LDO. Low-noise LDO (U9, ADP7142, fixed 5.0 V) post-regulating the +5 V analog rail. It takes the TPS63802 buck-boost's raw output (TPS63802_VOUT, set to ~5.5 V) and scrubs the switching ripple to produce a quiet +5 V for the op-amp positive supply and the LM27761 negative-rail generator. C23 is the input cap, C24 the output cap, and C25 (on SS) sets the soft-start ramp."
    (at 231.14 162.56 0) (size 58.42 17.78)
    (stroke (width 0) (type default))
    (fill (type color) (color 255 255 194 1))
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27) bold) (justify left top))
    (uuid 450f6923-0c40-4067-afb2-5b2663f0e7be)
  )
  (text_box "Description: Fuel Gauge (MAX17048). I²C battery monitor (U3) measuring cell state-of-charge. CELL/VDD tie to DEV_BATT+ with bypass C3 (0.1 µF); SDA/SCL/ALRT (MAX17048_*) report to the MCU; CTG/QSTRT/GND/EP per datasheet.\n"
    (at 281.94 83.82 0) (size 114.3 10.16)
    (stroke (width 0) (type default))
    (fill (type color) (color 255 255 194 1))
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27) bold) (justify left top))
    (uuid 460e3a50-47a4-4771-9780-0a9c1a5714ec)
  )
  (text_box "Description: Li-Ion Charger & Power Path (BQ24075). Charger (U2) fed from BQ24075_VIN; powers the system at OUT (BQ24075_OUT) while charging the cell at BAT (DEV_BATT+). Configuration via SYSOFF/CE/EN1/EN2, charge/input current set by R5/R4 (ISET/ILIM), safety timer R3 (TMR), IN cap C1, BAT/OUT bulk caps C2/C4, and status LEDs D1/D2 (R6/R7). TS (BQ24075_TS) is the battery-temperature input."
    (at 281.94 25.4 0) (size 114.3 10.16)
    (stroke (width 0) (type default))
    (fill (type color) (color 255 255 194 1))
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27) bold) (justify left top))
    (uuid 74441f07-a928-496a-aacc-9b96da0ec6ec)
  )
  (text_box "Description: Source OR-ing. Schottky diode-OR (D3/D4, ~0.3 V) combining USBC_VOUT and TPS54360_VOUT into BQ24075_VIN - whichever source is higher feeds the charger; the lower one's diode reverse-biases."
    (at 228.6 83.82 0) (size 48.26 15.24)
    (stroke (width 0) (type default))
    (fill (type color) (color 255 255 194 1))
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27) bold) (justify left top))
    (uuid 8374d2eb-a426-4203-b9b4-7d3cddc5502a)
  )
  (text_box "Description: 3.0 V Precision Reference. Voltage reference (U8, REF3030) providing a stable, accurate +3V0 rail used as the ADC reference for the acquisition front end. Powered from +3V3 with bypass cap C21; the precision 3.0 V output defines the ADC's full-scale span independently of the noisy supply rails, so measured voltages stay accurate."
    (at 142.24 220.98 0) (size 83.82 12.7)
    (stroke (width 0) (type default))
    (fill (type color) (color 255 255 194 1))
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27) bold) (justify left top))
    (uuid 85d14a19-8343-4d62-9f37-8142241da30a)
  )
  (text_box "Description: Battery / Power Connectors. Screw/JST terminals: J2 = EXT_BATT+ (the 12 V vehicle feed) and J3 = DEV_BATT+ (the lithium cell). Two distinct power sources, clearly separated.\n"
    (at 25.4 83.82 0) (size 111.76 7.62)
    (stroke (width 0) (type default))
    (fill (type color) (color 255 255 194 1))
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27) bold) (justify left top))
    (uuid 97b27502-601b-4a76-a354-a7ce523a524f)
  )
  (text_box "Description: 3.3 V Digital Rail (buck-boost). Single-inductor buck-boost regulator (U5, TPS63802) producing the main +3V3 logic supply from the charger's BQ24075_OUT rail. Because OUT swings from ~4.7 V (charging) down to ~3.0 V (low battery), a buck-boost is used so the output stays regulated whether the input is above or below 3.3 V. The external inductor (L2) bridges the L1/L2 switch nodes; R16/R17 set the output via the FB divider; R18 enables the device; C13/C14 provide input/output decoupling.\n"
    (at 25.4 162.56 0) (size 111.76 12.7)
    (stroke (width 0) (type default))
    (fill (type color) (color 255 255 194 1))
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27) bold) (justify left top))
    (uuid b46cef4b-4670-497a-9d4c-4e7a80d7897b)
  )
  (text_box "Description: 12 V Buck (TPS54360 → ~5.2 V). Wide-input automotive step-down (U4) converting the protected vehicle rail TPS54360_VIN down to TPS54360_VOUT (~5.2 V with the present R13/R14 divider). Includes input caps C5/C6, EN/UVLO divider R10/R11, frequency-set R9 on RT/CLK, BOOT cap C7, inductor L1 with catch diode D5, output caps C8/C9, and the COMP network R12/C10/C11."
    (at 142.24 25.4 0) (size 134.62 10.16)
    (stroke (width 0) (type default))
    (fill (type color) (color 255 255 194 1))
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27) bold) (justify left top))
    (uuid ef585229-6a0c-4f2d-b159-eb03d4a81c00)
  )

